description: Intensive care units are now beginning to fill, the World Health Organization tells the BBC.
title: Coronavirus: Europe's daily deaths rise by nearly 40% compared with last week - WHO
title_page: Coronavirus: Europe's daily deaths rise by nearly 40% compared with last week - WHO - BBC News
maintext: In Moscow, more than 1,000 Covid patients are admitted to hospital each day. But the facemask rules in the capital have already been tightened, and clubbers and bar-goers already have to register their phones. City officials say the rate of new infections has been slowing, so they won't force venues to implement the new curfew - or close "any sectors of the economy" - for now.
